---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
const title = 'Privacy Policy | divorcesettlementcalc.com';
const description = 'Privacy policy for divorcesettlementcalc.com — data collection, the case-review form, cookies, and third-party services.';
---
<BaseLayout title={title} description={description}>
  <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
  <p><strong>Last updated:</strong> July 2026</p>

  <h2>Information we collect</h2>
  <p>Browsing divorcesettlementcalc.com — using the calculator or reading the guides — does not collect any personal information. All calculator inputs are processed locally in your browser and are not transmitted to our servers. No account registration is required.</p>
  <p>If you submit the Divorce case-review form on our homepage, we collect your name, phone number, email address, the case details you enter, and a timestamp of your consent. That information is only collected if you choose to submit the form.</p>

  <h2>How case-review form information is shared</h2>
  <p>If you submit the case-review form, your name, phone number, email address, and case details are shared with one or more attorneys or their agents licensed to practice in your jurisdiction, so they can evaluate your situation and contact you about it. The Click Lab Agency LLC, which operates divorcesettlementcalc.com, is not a law firm, does not provide legal advice, and does not vet, endorse, or guarantee the attorneys in this network. Submitting the form does not create an attorney-client relationship with The Click Lab Agency LLC or with any attorney until and unless that attorney separately agrees to represent you. The Click Lab Agency LLC may be compensated for these referrals.</p>
  <p>By submitting the form, you separately consent to be contacted by phone, text, and email — including by automated dialing technology — by The Click Lab Agency LLC and the attorneys or agents your information is shared with. That consent is not required to use any other part of this site, and you can decline it by not submitting the form.</p>

  <h2>Cookies and advertising</h2>
  <p>This site uses Google AdSense to display advertisements. Google AdSense sets cookies to serve relevant ads based on your browsing activity. These cookies are set by Google, not by divorcesettlementcalc.com, and are subject to Google&rsquo;s privacy policy. You can manage your Google ad preferences at <a href="https://adssettings.google.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener">adssettings.google.com</a>.</p>

  <h2>Analytics</h2>
  <p>We use Google Analytics (property G-3G26YHGS73) to collect aggregate traffic data — page views, session counts, and general geographic distribution. This data is anonymized and used only to understand site usage patterns. We do not use it to identify individual visitors. Google Analytics data is subject to Google&rsquo;s privacy policy.</p>

  <h2>Third-party services</h2>
  <p>Beyond Google AdSense and Google Analytics — both operated by Google LLC and subject to Google&rsquo;s <a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Privacy Policy</a> — the only other party that may receive your information is the attorney network described above, and only if you submit the case-review form. We do not sell or share personal information with any other third party.</p>

  <h2>Your choices and opt-out</h2>
  <p>The simplest opt-out is not to submit the case-review form — browsing the calculator and guides never shares any personal information. If you have already submitted the form and want your information removed or want to withdraw consent to be contacted, email <a href="mailto:hey@theclicklab.agency">hey@theclicklab.agency</a> with the subject line <strong>[OPT-OUT]</strong>, or visit <a href="https://theclicklab.agency/optout" target="_blank" rel="noopener">theclicklab.agency/optout</a>. You can also opt out of Google&rsquo;s interest-based advertising at <a href="https://adssettings.google.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Google Ad Settings</a>, or install the <a href="https://tools.google.com/dlpage/gaoptout" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Google Analytics Opt-out Browser Add-on</a>.</p>

  <h2>California privacy rights (CCPA/CPRA)</h2>
  <p>Sharing case-review form information with attorneys in exchange for compensation may be considered a &ldquo;sale&rdquo; or &ldquo;share&rdquo; of personal information under the California Consumer Privacy Act and its amendments. California residents may opt out of this sharing at any time using either method above. Anonymous browsing of the calculator and guides is never sold or shared, because it collects no personal information in the first place. California residents also have the right to know what personal information we hold, to request deletion, and to non-discrimination for exercising these rights — contact us at the email above to make a request.</p>

  <h2>European privacy rights (GDPR)</h2>
  <p>If you are located in the EU/EEA or UK, the legal basis for processing information you submit through the case-review form is your consent, given at the point of submission. You can withdraw that consent at any time using the opt-out methods above; withdrawal does not affect the lawfulness of processing that occurred before withdrawal. Browsing the calculator and guides involves no personal-data processing and requires no legal basis.</p>

  <h2>Contact</h2>
  <p>Questions about this privacy policy, or requests regarding your data? Email <a href="mailto:hey@theclicklab.agency">hey@theclicklab.agency</a>.</p>
</BaseLayout>
